==English==

===Pronunciations===
# {{audio|en-us-fillet-meat.ogg|Audio (US) fil-AY}} - ''pronunciation one''
# {{audio|en-us-fillet-round.ogg|Audio (US) FILL-et}} - ''pronunciation two''

===Noun===
'''fillet'''  
*Pronunciation one:
*# A [[strip]] or [[compact]] [[piece]] of [[meat]] or [[fish]] from which any [[bone]]s have been [[remove]]d.
*Pronunciation two:
*# (''architecture'') A thin flat [[moulding]] used as [[separation]] between larger moldings
*# A [[rounded]] [[relief]] or [[cut]] at an [[edge]], especially an inside edge, added for a finished appearance and to break sharp edges.  
*# A type of [[weld]] that creates a rounded [[bead]] at an inside corner.
*#:''Place a '''fillet''' weld at the joint.

====Translations====
*French: [[filet]] ''m''

===Verb===
'''to fillet'''  ([[fillets]], [[filleted]], [[filleting]])
*Pronunciation one:
*# To [[slice]], [[bone]] or make into fillets.
*Pronunciation two:
*# To [[apply]], [[create]], or [[specify]] a rounded or filled corner.

====Translations====
*French: désosser

